# Cursor Rules for Portfolio EDC

## Project Overview
Modern portfolio website built with Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, and shadcn/ui components.

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Prefer functional components with hooks
- Use 'use client' directive for client-side components
- Follow ESLint rules (no unescaped entities, etc.)
- Use proper React patterns (avoid setState in useEffect body)

## Component Guidelines
- Place reusable components in `/components`
- Use shadcn/ui components from `/components/ui`
- Always include proper TypeScript types
- Add accessibility attributes (aria-labels, roles, etc.)
- Support dark mode with theme-aware styling

## Animation Guidelines
- Use Framer Motion for complex animations
- Always respect `usePrefersReducedMotion` hook
- Keep animations subtle and purposeful
- Use Tailwind transitions for simple hover effects

## Data Fetching
- Use TanStack Query hooks from `/hooks/use-api.ts`
- Always provide mock data fallbacks
- Handle loading and error states

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow shadcn/ui patterns for consistency
- Support light and dark modes
- Ensure WCAG 2.1 AA compliance

## Testing
- Run `npm run lint` before committing
- Build with `npm run build` to catch TypeScript errors
- Test on mobile and desktop viewports
- Verify accessibility with browser DevTools

## File Naming
- Use kebab-case for files: `my-component.tsx`
- Use PascalCase for components: `MyComponent`
- Use camelCase for utilities: `myUtilFunction`

## Git Workflow
- Use conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, etc.)
- Keep commits focused and atomic
- Update documentation when adding features

